        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 3 at 10:43PM CDT until June 3 at 11:15PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 1042 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 9 miles southeast
of Fort Gates, or 12 miles southeast of Gatesville, moving east at 15
mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters. At 1025 PM CDT...quarter size
hail was reported in Flat with this storm.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Pendleton, Whitson, Moffat, Mother Neff State Park, Owl Creek, Leon
Junction, Meadow Grove, Moody, Mound, Flat, The Grove, Morgan's Point
Resort, White Hall, Temple, and Belton Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection stay inside a sturdy structure and keep away from
windows.</instruction>
